reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 16, 2024
reviews.reviewText: These night stands were a bit smaller that I had expected, but that’s on me for not reading the sizing. These would be perfect for a kids bedroom or next to your couches in the living room! The charging station works so great and is so convenient as you can have multiple things plugged in at once (5 to be exact). These are greatly made and look very nice.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 5, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars Not worth buying honestly
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. It’s a cute night stand but I don’t like how the drawer has no drawer runners… because of this, the drawer can fall out if you pull it out too much. Also the “feet” for the bottom do not fit (the pieces I have pictured in my hand.) I saw one or two reviews on here where people got them on so maybe I just got defective parts. Just not worth it in my opinion!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 27, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I wasn't expecting them to be as solid as they are. Having the built in outlets are awesome. The drawers are a good size too. We use them in our livingroom and we wanted simple and functional, which is what we got.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Very heavy and sturdy
reviews.reviewText: Love these stands. I was very surprised at how heavy they were. Very good quality for your money. The directions for these stands could be a little better. But was able to put both stands together. I am using this as a night stand. Which this is actually shorter than most night stands. The picture of these are deceiving. I was thinking one stand would be taller than the other. But they are both the same height. Which is only 22 inches tall. So if you are wanting something taller, you may want to look at something else. That is why I gave them 4 stars. Overall very good product for your money.
